author: Adam Harding
title: NJ news: Thieves steal luxury handbags from Montclair store – NBC New York
text: The four suspects struck in the middle of the night at the store in Montclair, forcing their way in through the window. They can be seen on the video blowing right past a rack of clothes, instead heading right for the designer handbag that were on a back wall. In less than a minute, the thieves were gone. "They were in and out in 40 seconds. So they knew where to go. Obviously we were scoped out beforehand because they knew exactly where to go," said Arlene Carrini, the owner of the shop. "We had just done a Tiktok — we normally don’t keep all of the high end designer bags together." Get Tri-state area news and weather forecasts to your inbox. [Sign up for NBC New York newsletters.] The merchandise at the boutique is half consignment, half brand new. And while she didn't want to say what the exact value of the stolen bags was, Carrini called it "a significant amount" in lost profit. "It was heart-wrenching, like I was punched in the gut. It’s such a loss that you feel," she told NBC New York. Carrini and her husband took to social media earlier in the week to warn the community. She said other consignment shops have since come forward with similar stories. News "I would assume that they come in and they learn the lay of the land beforehand, just from what the detectives tell us and from speaking with other consignment shops who’ve reached out, who saw our post on social media, and said the same thing happened to them," she said. The masked men could be seen on security camera footage getting away in a BMW. The front window of the store was replaced soon after, but the shelves remain empty. "I just would love to protect the retail consignment world and just forewarn everyone that they should probably come up with other security measures," said Carrini. "I’m sure things will change but I don’t know how. Day by day, we’ll be doing what we need to do." Montclair police did not respond to a request for comment.

title: Metalpha Reports a Nearly Tripled Revenue Surge & First Positive Annual Profit in FY2025
text:
HONG KONG , July 31, 2025 /PRNewswire/ -- Metalpha Technology Holding Limited (Nasdaq: MATH ) (the "Company" or "Metalpha"), through its subsidiaries, is dedicated to providing digital asset-focused wealth management services with a full-service, institutional-grade platform. The Company today announced its audited financial results for the fiscal year ended March 31, 2025 .
FY2025 Annual Results Highlights
For the fiscal year ended March 31, 2025 , Metalpha achieved $44.6 million in income from wealth management business, which was 266% of the amount for the prior year. Net profit reached $15.9 million , a significant turnaround from a net loss of $3.7 million for the prior year.

"Last fiscal year marked a transformative growth for Metalpha. The mass adoption of digital assets and increasing global regulation clarity provided a pivotal opportunity for us to shape the future of digital asset wealth management." Said Adrian Wang , CEO of Metalpha. "By leveraging our expertise spanning both digital assets and traditional financial markets, we are committed to delivering superior institutional-grade solutions – empowering clients to navigate digital asset opportunities with confidence. Exceeding client expectations remains our core mission."
The Company filed its annual report on Form 20-F for the fiscal year ended March 31, 2025 (the "2025 Annual Report") with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission (the "SEC") on July 30, 2025. The 2025 Annual Report contains the Company's audited financial statements for the fiscal year ended March 31, 2025 , and is available on the SEC's website at www.sec.gov .
About Metalpha
Metalpha Technology Holding Limited (Nasdaq: MATH), through its subsidiaries, is dedicated to providing digital asset-focused wealth management services with a full-service, institutional-grade platform. With dedicated blockchain expertise, the Company aims to become a leader in the field of digital asset-based wealth management services, bringing robust innovation and transparency to the customers and businesses it serves.

author: Amaris Encinas
title: Gypsy Rose marks release from prison with Instagram selfie
text: Gypsy Rose makes first social media post, shares selfie after release from prison [Amaris Encinas](https://www.usatoday.com/staff/5133245001/amaris-encinas/) [Gypsy Rose Blanchard](/story/news/nation/2023/12/27/gypsy-rose-blanchard-release-case-timeline/72038395007/) commemorated her first full day of freedom with a selfie. She [ took to Instagram Friday](https://www.instagram.com/p/C1cNGBvu7IK/?utm_source=ig_embed&utm_campaign=loading) to mark her release from prison by snapping a quick pic of her smiling, writing “First selfie of freedom!” in the caption. [Embedded content: https://www.instagram.com/p/C1cNGBvu7IK/?utm_source=ig_embed&utm_campaign=loading](https://www.instagram.com/p/C1cNGBvu7IK/?utm_source=ig_embed&utm_campaign=loading) Blanchard, who conspired with her then-boyfriend Nick Godejohn to [kill her abusive mother in 2015](/story/news/local/2017/05/10/gypsy-blanchard-everything-you-need-know-case/101499166/), was released from prison [early Thursday morning. ](/story/news/nation/2023/12/28/gypsy-rose-blanchard-release-thursday/72047355007/) She pled [guilty to a second-degree murder charge](/story/news/crime/2016/07/05/gypsy-blanchard-pleads-guilty-murder/86617662/) on Tuesday, July 5, 2016 served about 85% of her 10-year sentence, spending a total of eight years behind bars for her role in the murder. She became eligible for parole in September. Blanchard also [ announced recently announced the release of an eBook titled “Release,”](/story/news/crime/2023/12/19/social-media-accounts-promote-gypsy-rose-blanchard-book-released/71966263007/) set to come out on Jan. 9. Here’s what we know about Gypsy Rose Blanchard. Who is Gypsy Rose? Gypsy, who is Clauddine “Dee Dee” Blanchard’s daughter, was made to believe she suffered from a wide range of medical ailments including leukemia, asthma and muscular dystrophy thanks to her mother. Gypsy’s late mother was accused of having made her daughter appear to have a range of physical and developmental ailments, USA Today previously [reported. ](/story/news/nation/2023/12/28/gypsy-rose-blanchard-release-thursday/72047355007/) Dee Dee Blanchard, later said to have [Munchausen syndrome by proxy](/story/news/crime/2016/07/06/munchausen-expert-says-gypsy-blanchard-case-unprecedented/86763054/) which is a mental condition in which someone makes another person ill for sympathy or gain received disability payments and gifts from charities all of Gypsy’s illnesses, that often led to painful treatment and procedures. Gypsy, who used a [wheelchair before it was discovered she could walk](/story/news/crime/2015/06/16/daughter-boyfriend-charged-murder-dee-dee-blancharde/28803189/), said she was desperate to escape her mother's abuse and sought help from her online boyfriend, Nicholas Godejohn. [Godejohn, who was was sentenced to life in prison](/story/news/crime/2019/02/22/nicholas-godejohn-sentenced-life-prison-blanchard-murder/2949249002/) for stabbing and killing Dee Dee Blanchard traveled to Missouri on [ June 9, 2015](/story/news/local/ozarks/2015/06/15/greene-county-sheriffs-office-searching-mother-daughter/71236652/) to help enact the escape plan. He was reportedly let into the home after Gypsy’s late mother fell asleep and used a knife handed to him by Gypsy to stab the sleeping woman 17 times, killing her before fleeing to his native Wisconsin, USA Today previously reported. Gypsy later told [ABC 20/20 news](https://abcnews.go.com/US/young-wheelchair-bound-woman-treated-illnesses-ended-prison/story?id=52138979) she hid in the bathroom with hands over her ears during the act. Authorities were contacted about a post on Dee Dee Blanchard’s Facebook page dated June 14, 2015 that read, ‘That B*** is dead!’ before her body was [ found in her home](/story/news/local/ozarks/2015/06/15/greene-county-sheriffs-office-searching-mother-daughter/71236652/) with multiple stab wounds. Before Gypsy was publicly tied to the murder, many Springfield residents were worried that she was also in peril. The bizarre nature of the Springfield murder made national headlines and became the subject of [documentaries](/story/news/local/ozarks/2017/05/10/prior-premiere-hbo-film-gypsys-father-and-filmmaker-speak-bizarre-case/101438406/) and [streamed television series](/story/news/local/ozarks/2019/03/20/the-act-hulu-dee-dee-gypsy-rose-blanchard-true-crime/3228086002/). When was Gypsy Rose arrested? Gypsy and her boyfriend were arrested on [June 14, 2015 in Big Bend, Wis. ](/story/news/nation/2023/12/27/gypsy-rose-blanchard-release-case-timeline/72038395007/) The pair posted two updates on Dee Dee Blanchard’s Facebook page earlier that day to draw attention to her yet undiscovered body. How old is Gypsy Rose? Gypsy Blanchard was born July 29, 1991, making her 32 years old in 2023. How old was Dee Dee Blanchard when she died? Dee Dee Blanchard was born May 3, 1967, making her 48 years old when she was killed in 2015. Who is Gypsy Rose married to? Gypsy married Ryan Scott Anderson in July 2022. Anderson is 37-year-old teacher based in Lake Charles, Louisiana, according to “ [People](https://www.msn.com/en-us/news/crime/gypsy-rose-blanchard-released-from-10-year-prison-sentence-early-after-mothers-murder-im-ready-exclusive/ar-AA1m9Bbi).” The pair split after three months of marriage but eventually reconciled, the magazine reported. She shared with various news outlets that she planned on attending a Kansas City Chiefs game with her husband after her release, stating that she hopes she gets to meet superstar Taylor Swift, who is dating Chiefs tight end Travis Kelce, USA Today previously [ reported. ](/story/news/nation/2023/12/28/gypsy-rose-blanchard-release-thursday/72047355007/)

author: mdzol.com
title: El gol de la TV Pública en el rating con la derrota de Argentina ante Marruecos en los Juegos Olímpicos de París - MDZ Online
text: El gol de la TV Pública en el rating con la derrota de Argentina ante Marruecos en los Juegos Olímpicos de París Tras el decepcionante resultado que obtuvo la Selección argentina este miércoles, se dio a conocer la notable medición que obtuvo el evento en el canal estatal. Este miércoles, la controversial derrota de Argentina ante Marruecos en los [Juegos Olímpicos de París 2024](https://www.mdzol.com/temas/juegos-olimpicos-de-paris-2024-80507.html) dio la vuelta al mundo, y la [TV Pública](https://www.mdzol.com/temas/tv-publica-8300.html) consiguió con el evento una buena marca en el [rating](https://www.mdzol.com/temas/rating-919.html), si se la compara con los números que suele conseguir con su programación habitual el canal estatal. La caída de la Selección argentina en el partido disputado contra Marruecos en los Juegos Olímpicos de París 2024 por 2-1, consiguió un promedio de 4.1 puntos de rating en la TV Pública, la señal encargada de seguir las instancias del desempeño de los deportistas argentinos de distintas disciplinas que participan de la importante contienda deportiva. Además, durante la jornada de este miércoles la TV Pública regristró buenas mediciones con la cobertura de otras competencias de los Juegos Olímpicos de París 2024, obteniendo marcas que oscilaron entre los 2.1 y los 3.3 puntos de rating. Más allá de la atención que genera el evento que se desarrolla en la capital francesa, Telefe logró instalar tres de sus propuestas como las más vistas del día en el top 5, ya que Survivor: Expedición Robinson se ubicó en el primer lugar con 10.2 puntos de rating, seguido de Escape perfecto con 9.3 en el segundo puesto y Telefe Noticias en la tercera posición con 7.6. Por otro lado, en El Trece lo más visto fue Los 8 Escalones de los 3 Millones con 7.4 puntos de rating, mientras que en El Nueve se impuso Bendita con 3.7, y en canal América LAM con 3.3. Respecto al destino del rating que logre la Televisión Pública con los Juegos Olímpicos de París 2024, el suceso estará determinado por la performance que alcancen las delegaciones argentinas de distintas disciplinas que pelean por traer alguna medalla al país. author: Stephanie Zoer, Freelance Reporter
title: E. Bourassa and Sons challenge businesses for the Carlyle food bank - SaskToday.ca
text: CARLYLE Each year E. Bourassa and Sons in Carlyle hold a toy drive for the local food bank. Although they already collected many items for this, they felt they could do more and wanted to do something different this year. The idea for a fundraiser was born out of the Weyburn branch being challenged by another business. Karley Hislop brought the idea forward to the group, and Carlyle's Bourassa branch decided to try a similar activity. On Dec. 6, the challenge began with Bourassa purchasing 24 items or more for the Carlyle District Food Bank, by which they challenged three other local businesses to purchase 24 items for the food bank and gave them 24 hours to bring the items to the branch. These three businesses would then nominate a business or two of their choice to do the same. This went on until Dec. 15 in the afternoon when the challenge was completed and items were delivered to the food bank. The challenge took off like wildfire and escalated into something much bigger than was anticipated. The organizers were overwhelmed with the success. Tina Renner, administrator for E. Bourassa and Sons said 63 businesses accepted the challenge with many of them bringing in much more than 24 items. Renner and E. Bourassa thanked all the businesses that took part in this challenge, making it such a success. Over 1,600 non-perishable and hygiene items were received and delivered to the food bank. The branch said they plan to continue with the challenge in the future as Carlyle knocked this one out of the park. E. Bourassa and Sons began their business in Carlyle in April 2018. The local office just celebrated its fifth year and now has 13 employees.
